Etymology. This new species is named in honor of the late distinguished physical oceanographer Columbus O. Iselin (
1904–1971
), after whom the University of Miami’s research ship, the R/V Columbus Iselin was named.

Remaining proximal stalk attached to aboral cup of 11 complete and 2 incomplete columnals (
Figure 2
). Stalk diameter decreasing from proximalmost ( 3.5 mm ) to 11 th columnal ( 3.1 mm ); columnal height respectively increasing from 0.4 mm to 0.7 mm .

Distribution. The species is known off the Bahamas , western tropical Atlantic Ocean, from depths of 4,243 to 4,558 meters (
Fig. 7
).
